Alice_Rawsthorn
'''Alice Rawsthorn'''  (born 1958 in ), Debrett's is a British design critic, who writes on design in the international edition of ''''. She also writes the "By Design" column for '''' magazine. A trustee of the  and the Michael Clark Company, the contemporary dance group, she is chair of the board of trustees at the  in London. Her latest book ''Hello World: Where Design Meets Life'' explores design's impact on our lives: past, present and future.
==Education and early career in journalism==
After graduating in art and architectural history from , Rawsthorn won a place on the graduate trainee journalism scheme of the , then became media editor of '''' magazine. In 1985, she joined the staff of the '''', where she worked as a foreign correspondent in Paris and pioneered the paper's coverage of the creative industries before becoming architecture and design critic in 2000.
